What I understand about Gnocchi so far:
[Rst primer](http://sphinx-doc.org/rest.html#rst-primer)

SHOWTREEHERE

Gnocchi is split up into the rest folder, which has the functions that control the api, the storage folder, and the indexer folder, which contains the driver information for swift. 

The storage driver stores the timestamps and values, the indexer stores the databout the resource and entity. Carbonara is the library that implements the time series manipulation. The __init__ files hold most of the important information.

